專輯的名稱原本被認為是《我的另類羅曼史之起落》（The Rise and Fall of My Chemical Romance），不過在《Kerrang!》的專訪中傑洛德表示，這只是專輯的製作代稱，他說「這絕對不是專輯的名稱，只是開玩笑的而已」。<ref>原文為："It was never the title of the album, more a spoof, or joke."</ref><ref name="blackparade">{{cite web
 |url         = http://www.theblackparade.com
 |publisher   = Theblackparade.com
 |title       = The Black Parade
 |deadurl     = yes
 |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20061017195024/http://www.theblackparade.com/
 |archivedate = 2006-10-17
}}</ref>

在2006年8月23日，《黑暗行軍》（The Black Parade）專輯中的兩支單曲《Welcome to the Black Parade》（黑暗行軍）和《Famous Last Words》（最後遺言）的音樂綠影帶拍攝完成，預計在2007年1月22日推出。<ref name="Billboard">{{Cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?pid=489806&aid=812296 |title=存档副本 |access-date=2006-12-11 |archive-date=2008-12-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081229055805/http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?pid=489806&aid=812296 |dead-url=no }}</ref>音樂錄影帶的導演是[[山繆·貝爾|山姆·貝爾]]，他曾指導過[[涅槃乐队|-{zh-hant: 超脫合唱團; zh-hans:涅槃乐队}-]]（Nirvana）的《Smells Like Teen Spirit》和[[年輕歲月|年輕歲月]]的《American Idiot》兩支[[音樂錄影帶|音樂錄影帶]]。<ref name="videostatic">
{{cite web
 | url= http://www.videostatic.com/vs/2006/week30/index.html#entry-11878537
 | publisher= VideoStatic
 | title= My Chemical Romance
 | access-date= 2006-12-11
 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070221054446/http://www.videostatic.com/vs/2006/week30/index.html#entry-11878537
 | archive-date= 2007-02-21
 | dead-url= yes
 }}
</ref>

在拍攝《Famous Last Words》音樂錄影帶期間，主唱傑洛德和鼓手巴柏受了傷。傑洛德的腳踝韌帶斷裂，這是由於法蘭克·伊羅在拍攝中途撲到傑洛德身上並把他推倒引致。而巴柏的腿被火焰灼傷，其後更受到[[葡萄球菌|葡萄球菌]]的感染，需要住院接受觀察。兩人的受傷讓樂團取消了好幾場演出。有許多的報導指出這些傷害是因為車禍造成，而根據樂團在 MySpace 網站的官方聲明，他們是在音樂錄影帶拍攝現場受的傷。<ref name="mychemicalromance">{{cite web
 |url=http://www.mychemicalromance.com/flashsite.php 
 |publisher=Mychemicalromance.com 
 |title=My Chemical Romance News 
 |deadurl=yes 
 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060819035603/http://www.mychemicalromance.com/flashsite.php 
 |archivedate=2006-08-19 
}}</ref><!--

[[File:Mcr_hammersmith_album_announcement.jpg|thumb]]
On [[August_22|August 22]], 2006, the band played a special one-off show at the 1800-capacity London [[Hammersmith_Palais|Hammersmith Palais]]. The show sold out in 15 minutes prompting tickets being sold on eBay well over the tickets' face value. The band is known to make an interesting creative appearance at these types of shows, such as arriving in coffins. The name of the album they promoted was announced and 20 people dressed in black capes with their faces obscured paraded around Hammersmith, followed by a large group of fans and street team members with signs saying "The Black Parade". Later during the show the album title and the UK release date were confirmed. Posters and stickers and a very small number of Black Parade T-Shirts were also given to people in the queue by the street team members. Prior to the band taking the stage it was announced that "My Chemical Romance" were unable to play, but they would be replaced by "The Black Parade". After initial crowd hostility it became clear the band were simply performing under a pseudonym in keeping with the theme of the album. When the set began, the backdrop art displayed the words "The Black Parade". New songs played included "House of Wolves", "The End", "Dead!", and live debuts for "I Don't Love You" and "Cancer". 

On September 2nd 2006, My Chemical Romance posted "Welcome to the Black Parade" on their Myspace page and their purevolume page. It can also be heard on the official website. <ref name="mychemicalromance">{{cite web
 | url= http://www.mychemicalromance.com
 | publisher= Mychemicalromance.com
 | title= My Chemical Romance}}</ref> "Welcome to the Black Parade" had its first radio airing on September 11th, 2006. On [[September_26|September 26]], [[2006|2006]] the "Welcome to the Black Parade" music video was released in the UK, and on  [[September_27|September 27]]in the US. <ref name="blackparade"/>

On October 9th, 2006, My Chemical Romance played at [[Spike_TV|Spike TV]]'s 2006 Scream Awards. Various street team members dressed up in white masks and others played drum cadences as the band was introduced. They played "Welcome to the Black Parade". <ref name="MCR At Spike Awards">{{cite web
 | url= http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LQL7MUbx-Rs
 | publisher= Youtube
 | title=MCR At Spike Awards}}</ref>

[[File:Mcrnewlogo.jpg|thumb]]
On October 12th, 2006, My Chemical Romance made a rare in-store performance to 500 fans at [[Virgin_Megastores|Virgin Megastores]] on London's [[Oxford_Street|Oxford Street]]. During the bands 35 minute set, they played "House of Wolves", "Famous Last Words" and "Welcome to the Black Parade" from ''The Black Parade'', alongside a handful of songs from the band's back catalogue. In order to get wristbands for the event, many fans slept outside the shop the previous night. British band [[Towers_Of_London|Towers Of London]] caused trouble at the event when the Towers guitarist, Dirk Tourette, allegedly flicked a cigarette butt at Bob Bryar while he was performing.<ref name="nme">{{cite web
 | url= http://www.nme.com/news/my-chemical-romance/24700
 | publisher= nme
 | title= My Chemical Romance News}}</ref> After the live performance, the band met fans and signed records for several hours.

"Welcome to the Black Parade" reached number one on October 15th, 2006, in the UK, giving them their first number one.

October 21, 2006 marked their first appearance on [[Saturday_Night_Live|Saturday Night Live]] as the musical guests.-->

專輯《[[黑暗行軍|黑暗行軍]]》（The Black Parade）分別於2006年10月23日和24日在英國及美國發行。 台灣隨後於2006年10月27日發行。<ref name=warner>[http://www.warnermusic.com.tw/music/album.php?id=3587 台灣代理商華納音樂的專輯介紹]{{Dead link|date=2019年6月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}（2006年12月12日查證）</ref> <!--

My Chemical Romance is playing six dates from [[January_19|January 19]] to [[February_4|February 4]], [[2007|2007]] in the world renowned [[Big_Day_Out|Big Day Out]] festival in Australia and New Zealand. They are billed alongside [[Tool_(band)|Tool]], [[Muse_(band)|Muse]], [[The_Killers_(band)|The Killers]], and [[Jet_(band)|Jet]].-->

=== 《危險時刻：扫兴侠的真實人生》（2009年—2011年） ===
2009年2月1日，我的另类罗曼史发布了一个名为《荒芜小巷》（Desolation Row）的新单曲（为[[鲍勃·迪伦|鲍勃·迪伦]]歌曲的翻唱），作为同年电影《[[守護者_(電影)|守望者]]》的片尾曲。<ref>{{cite web|title=New My Chemical Romance single, 'Desolation Row' on Xfm first|url=http://www.thrashhits.com/2009/01/new-my-chemical-romance-single-desolation-row-on-xfm-first/|access-date=2010-03-13|publisher=Thrashhits.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120213161442/http://www.thrashhits.com/2009/01/new-my-chemical-romance-single-desolation-row-on-xfm-first/|archive-date=2012-02-13|url-status=dead}}</ref>

2009年5月27日，乐队的网站宣布将在接下来的几周内与制作人Brendan O'Brien在录音室录制他们的第四张专辑。Gerard Way形容他的目标是做一张摇滚专辑<ref name="Interview with Gerard">{{cite web|title=My Chemical Romance Promise 'Punk Rock' Album|url=http://ultimate-guitar.com/news/upcoming_releases/my_chemical_romance_promise_punk_rock_album.html|access-date=2014-07-27|publisher=Ultimate-guitar.com|archive-date=2008-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080202075201/http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/upcoming_releases/my_chemical_romance_promise_punk_rock_album.html}}</ref>，这张专辑将会“充满仇恨”、不那么戏剧化，并希望捕捉现场演出中“车库摇滚的感觉和更多的能量”。<ref>{{cite web|title=My Chemical Romance on New Record: Less Drama, No Makeup|url=http://www.idiomag.com/peek/65600/my_chemical_romance|access-date=2009-02-19|date=2009-02-18|publisher=[[idiomag|idiomag]]|archive-date=2009-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090224172151/http://www.idiomag.com/peek/65600/my_chemical_romance}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=My Chemical Romance Full of Hate|url=http://www.popeater.com/music/article/my-chemical-romance-full-of-hate-on-new/220047|access-date=2009-06-30|publisher=Popeater|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090205185301/http://www.popeater.com/music/article/my-chemical-romance-full-of-hate-on-new/220047|archive-date=February 5, 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref>

2010年9月，专辑的先导影片出现在乐队YouTube页面；专辑的名称公布为《危險時刻：扫兴侠的真實人生》（Danger Days: The True Lives Of The Fabulous Killjoys）。9月22日，乐队在Zane Lowe主持的BBC Radio 1节目和洛杉矶的KROQ-FM电台首播了他们的歌曲《Na Na Na (Na Na Na Na)》<ref>{{cite web|title=World Premiere: My Chemical Romance "Na Na Na"|url=http://kroq.radio.com/2010/09/22/world-premiere-my-chemical-romance-na-na-na/|access-date=2010-09-22|date=2010-09-22|publisher=KROQ-FM|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100925193758/http://kroq.radio.com/2010/09/22/world-premiere-my-chemical-romance-na-na-na/|archive-date=2010-09-25|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=My Chemical Romance New Song and Interview|url=http://absolutepunk.net/showthread.php?t=1923042|access-date=2010-09-22|date=2010-09-22|website=AbsolutePunk|archive-date=2012-07-07|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120707064528/http://absolutepunk.net/showthread.php?t=1923042}}</ref>。专辑最终于2010年11月22日发行。<ref>{{cite web|title=Danger Days: The True Lives of the Fabulous Killjoys | My Chemical Romance | Album|url=http://www.mtv.com/music/artist/my_chemical_romance/albums.jhtml?albumId=2652454|access-date=2011-11-04|publisher=MTV}}</ref>

鼓手Bob Bryar于2010年3月3日离开乐队。<ref>{{cite web|title=One chapter ends and another begins ...|url=http://www.mychemicalromance.com/blog/frank/one-chapter-ends-and-another-begins|access-date=2010-03-13|date=2010-03-03|publisher=My Chemical Romance|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100307013124/http://www.mychemicalromance.com/blog/frank/one-chapter-ends-and-another-begins|archive-date=2010-03-07|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=AP: NEWS – Bob Bryar out of My Chemical Romance|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/8574.htm|access-date=2010-03-13|publisher=Altpress.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100312112709/http://www.altpress.com/news/8574.htm|archive-date=2010-03-12|url-status=dead}}</ref>Michael Pedicone在年底加入乐队，并取代他成为乐队鼓手。<ref>{{cite web|title=My Chemical Romance introduce new Killjoy, Michael Pedicone|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1650748/20101025/my_chemical_romance.jhtml|access-date=2010-10-25|date=2010-10-25|publisher=MTV|archive-date=2010-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101028025059/http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1650748/20101025/my_chemical_romance.jhtml}}</ref>但他因为涉嫌盗窃于2011年9月2日被乐队开除<ref>{{cite web|title=My Chemical Romance sack drummer Mike Pedicone over theft claims|url=https://www.nme.com/news/my-chemical-romance/59014|access-date=2014-07-27|publisher=Nme.com|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304044613/http://www.nme.com/news/my-chemical-romance/59014}}</ref><ref name="mychemicalromance1">{{cite web|title=Just The Facts|url=http://www.mychemicalromance.com/blog/frank/just-facts|access-date=2011-11-04|date=2011-09-02|publisher=My Chemical Romance|archive-date=2012-04-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120426162656/http://www.mychemicalromance.com/blog/frank/just-facts}}</ref>，并由贾罗德·亚历山大代替。

===《常规武器》和解散（2011年—2013年）===
樂隊於2013年3月23日宣佈解散，結束12年的生涯。

===樂團重組（2019年—）===
2019年10月31日，我的另類羅曼史在Instagram宣布將在12月20日於洛杉磯重组。<ref>{{Cite web|title=My Chemical Romance 在 Instagram 上发布：“Like phantoms forever. Are you excited?! Check @mychemicalromance post for tickets! // #mychemicalromance #mcr”|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B4S2JK1B44E/|accessdate=2019-11-01|website=Instagram}}</ref>

